Turkish Equity Movers: Fortis, Turk Ekonomi Bankasi, Zorlu Move

-- B y   B e n j a m i n   H a r v e y
-- 
2011-02-11T16:17:35Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-11/turkish-equity-movers-fortis-turk-ekonomi-bankasi-zorlu-move.html
Turkey’s benchmark  ISE National 100
Index  rose 308.82, or 0.5 percent, to 64,730.35 at 5:30 p.m.
close in Istanbul, trimming this week’s decline to 0.9 percent.  The following stocks were active. Symbols are in
parentheses.    Fortis Bank AS  (FORTS TI), the bank part-owned by BNP
Paribas SA that has agreed to a merger with  Turk Ekonomi Bankasi
AS  (TEBNK TI), known as TEB, dropped 6 kurus, or 2.9 percent, to
2.02 liras. The bank reported 2010 net income of 22.3 million
liras ($14 million), down from 111.2 million liras last year,
according to a company statement yesterday.  Turk Ekonomi Bankasi AS (TEBNK TI) declined 5 kurus, or 2.5
percent, to 1.97 liras. The bank part-owned by BNP Paribas SA of
France reported earnings rose to 300.3 million liras in 2010,
from 210.2 million liras. Most of the bank’s 2010 profit growth
came in the form of a 180 million-lira start-up fee for the
insurance business with Zurich Insurance AS, Alpay Dinckoc, an
analyst with Oyak Securities, said in a telephone interview.    Zorlu Enerji Elektrik Uretim AS  (ZOREN TI), an energy
company, rose 5 kurus, or 1.9 percent, to 2.69 liras after
reporting that it hired Credit Suisse Group AG for the possible
sale of shares in its unit Rotor Elektrik Uretim AS.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Benjamin Harvey in Istanbul at 
